olive oil
1 Potato
½ Red Onion
2 clove Garlic
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet Beef Mince
1 packet Diced Bacon
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
1 packet Worcestershire Sauce
1 packet Filo Pastry
1 Apple
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet roasted tomato salsa

• Preheat oven to 240ºC/220ºC fan-forced. Boil the kettle.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Finely chop onion (see ingredients) and garlic.

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water and add a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook potato and peeled pumpkin pieces in boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and lightly crush with fork.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook beef mince (no need for oil!), diced bacon and onion, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add Kiwi spice blend and garlic, and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add Worcestershire sauce and stir to combine, then remove from the heat.
• Add the crushed cooked veggies into the beef mixture and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Lay 1 filo pastry sheet on a dry surface and fold in half lengthways into a long strip. Spoon 2 heaped tablespoons of beef mixture at one end of the filo strip.
• Fold the pastry diagonally over the filling to form a triangle. Fold the triangle horizontally then upwards. Then fold it back over to the other side and continue like this, alternating upwards and then diagonally, until the end to make a triangular parcel.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Repeat for remaining filo sheets and beef mixture.
• Brush parcels with olive oil and bake until golden, 12-15 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple.
• In a medium bowl combine mixed salad leaves, apple, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide beef and bacon veggie Cornish-style pasties and apple salad between plates.
• Serve with roasted tomato salsa. Enjoy!